ov/nchs/data/nhanes/public/2017/labmethods/PBCD-J-PBY-J-R-MET-508.pdf). For urine samples, single random urine sample collection was adopted. Urine heavy metal levels were also directly measured by mass spectrometry following simple dilution. Detailed information on urine collection methods and laboratory procedures for urine heavy metal measurement can be accessed via the following NHANES links (https://wwwn.cdc.gov/nchs/data/nhanes/public/2015/labmethods/UTAS_UTASS_UM_UMS_I_MET.PDF, https://wwwn.cdc.gov/nchs/data/nhanes/public/2015/manuals/2016_MEC_Laboratory_Procedures_Manual.pdf). The Systemic Inflammatory Response Index (SIRI) is one of the important indicators currently used to reflect systemic inflammatory status32. It assesses the degree of inflammation by considering the ratio of neutrophil to lymphocyte counts in peripheral blood. Therefore, this study selected SIRI as an indicator of participants’ inflammatory levels.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
